###########MATERIALS
###########
########### Mars material
Material MarsMaterial young 21.5e9 alpha 0.3 density 2200 ft 2100000.0 Gt 50
###########
########### Fatigue shear material
###########Material FatigueMaterial E0 35e9 alpha 0.300000 density 2200.0 fc 20e6 ft 3.5e6 KinN 4e9 gammaN 20e9 m -0.2e-6 Ad 4000e-6 tauBar 4.0e6 Kin 0 gamma 10.0e9 S 0.0025e3 a 0
###########
########### Transport material
Material TrsprtMaterial	capacity	0.001	density	1.00E+03	permeability	1.00E-18	viscosity	8.90E-04	crack_turtuosity	0.9 biot_coeff 0
###########Elastic material
Material DisMechMaterial young 21.5e9 alpha 0.3 density 2200
###########dalsi mars
###########Material MarsMaterial young 21.5e9 alpha 0.3 density 2200 ft 21000000.0 Gt 500
###########dalsi TrsprtMaterial
###########Material TrsprtMaterial	capacity	11.000000	permeability 22e-18 viscosity 1e-5 crack_turtuosity 0.5 density	1e3
###########
###########
###########
###########
###########
###########EXPORTERS
Exporter VTKElementExporter elems saveEvery 0.001 cellData 3 materialID damage crack_opening pointData 2 nodal_stress pressure
######################TXTGaussPointExporter txtout 13 x y normal_x normal_y damageT damageN strainTY strainTZ strainPLTY strainPLTZ stressN stressT1 stressT2 saveEvery 1e-3
